cs.DC, cs.DL, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the design and optimization of storage and data management resources for LHC computing, which involves distributed computing and data processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the performance analysis of the architecture and procedures to improve it, which falls under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of middleware and grid computing is also mentioned, which relates to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of analysis activity on other users of the system, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
